Elmwood, also known as the Watson-Mardre House, is a historic plantation house located near Windsor, Bertie County, North Carolina. It was built about 1836, and expanded between 1838 and 1863.  It is a two-story frame structure three bays wide and two deep, with Greek Revival and Federal style design elements.  It has a gable roof.  Also on the property are the contributing kitchen and dairy.It was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1982.


